getHostTimeForBeats

public long getHostTimeForBeats(double inBeats)
                         throws CAException
Returns a host time value for a given beats time based on the time that the sequence started playing. As this call is only valid if the player is playing this call will return an error if the player is not playing or the postion of the player (its "starting beat") when the player was started. (see the MusicSequence calls for beat<->seconds calls for these speculations) This call is totally dependent on the Sequence attached to the Player, (primarily the tempo map of the Sequence), so the player must have a sequence attached to it or an error is returned.

CoreAudio::MusicPlayerGetHostTimeForBeats

Throws:
CAException

getBeatsForHostTime

public double getBeatsForHostTime(long inHostTime)
                           throws CAException
Returns a time in beats given a host time based on the time that the sequence started playing. As this call is only valid if the player is playing this call will return an error if the player is not playing, or if inHostTime is sometime before the Player was started. (see the MusicSequence calls for beat<->seconds calls for these speculations) This call is totally dependent on the Sequence attached to the Player, (primarily the tempo map of the Sequence), so the player must have a sequence attached to it or an error is returned.

CoreAudio::MusicPlayerGetBeatsForHostTime

CAException

isPlaying

public boolean isPlaying()
                  throws CAException
This call returns a non-zero value in outIsPlaying if the player has been started and not stopped. It may have "played" past the valid events of the attached MusicSequence, but it is still considered to be playing (and its time value increasing) in that situation.

CoreAudio::MusicPlayerIsPlaying
